{"questionId":"20391","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>90</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> and the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> intersect at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math> has a gradient of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and is a tangent to the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> at the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The shaded region <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> is enclosed by the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> and the lines <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/1a9ac0d854056c84c90d6c109e3ed2658a603e40.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinate of the point where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math> intersects the line <math xmlns=\"